  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The hemolysis power-law damage accumulation model employed here is grounded in the mechanistic framework described in the foundational turbulent-stress hemolysis study indexed at https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003, which provides the scalar stress exposure methodology underpinning the RH index computation used throughout this assessment.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "referencesIdentifier": "https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003",
